      • getPreConditionChildren

        public List<Object> getPreConditionChildren()
        Gets the value of the preConditionChildren property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the preConditionChildren property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getPreConditionChildren().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list ChangeLogPropertyDefined TableIsEmpty ForeignKeyConstraintExists ExpectedQuotingStrategy IndexExists SqlCheck TableExists And RowCount Element Object ChangeSetExecuted Dbms ViewExists ColumnExists CustomPrecondition Not Or SequenceExists PrimaryKeyExists RunningAs
